Explanation:
cmdbApplicationId: This is the unique identifier for the CMDB application you want to associate with the Application Set. It helps the system identify the specific application in the CMDB.
cmdbApplicationDescription: This is a human-readable description of the CMDB application. It is usually the application name or a brief description of what the application does.
Where to Include cmdbApplicationId:
cmdbApplicationId should be included at the root level of your application_set_data dictionary.
You retrieve this value using your get_cmdb_application_by_id function and pass it to the create_application_set_in_asset_store function.

